  "body": "One of the ESIPP e2e tests is currently broken on HEAD: https://k8s-testgrid.appspot.com/google-gce#gce-alpha-features\r\n\r\nFailures all follow below pattern:\r\n- Create an OnlyLocal Loadbalancer Service\r\n- Create a backend pod on node1\r\n- Test only node1 responses 200 OK for health check\r\n- Delete this backend pod and create another pod on node2\r\n- Test only node2 responses 200 OK for health check\r\n- node1 still responses 200 OK --- test fails\r\n\r\nTook a look at the codes, found the bug is that kube-proxy health check does not refresh local endpoints count when local endpoints don't exist anymore ([codes](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/859b97b5512e2518e098cccfb1bdff93435e2cdf/pkg/proxy/healthcheck/healthcheck.go#L216-L229)).\r\n\r\n@thockin @freehan ",
